Description: Fragment of flattened handle at neck join of a pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine light red-brown; white inclusions. Circular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 28, 8? Relatively small handle.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (ID.122)
